content: The concept is unique and yet it brought back so many memories of Zelda Link's Awakening and Survival Kids. It has this sense of planning; you have to be meticulous and think ahead to do things within the time limit. The time limit makes the small world feel bigger and very quickly yours. The game manages to deliver a message through its plot but also through its main mechanic which shows videogames can be a form of art. Not everyone will enjoy it but it is a very special game indeed!
It's a Great adventure game, with interesting puzzles to solve... the time mechanic makes it interesting... definitely one of the best on mobile
A very satisfying offline puzzle-adventure game! It throws you right in to the exploration and uses a very unique time system to any rpg I've ever played. Well done!

I generally love Devolver games, but this is one of the worst games I've ever played. The core conceit is that you die after a minute. But everything is one minute and 5 seconds away, or if you are doing a puzzle you're not entirely sure about, if you realise the solution just before you die, you'll walk slowly to the puzzle start and then by the time you get there, you'll have forgotten the solution. It's an exercise in frustration and tedium. A huge let down.
I normally dont play mobile games. But this is a hidden gem. Easily 5 star. Only one complaints: slightly awkward controls. Best mobile game ever.
Needs better movement controls. Apart from that, I'm really enjoying the concept of the 1-minute round.

This is like playing a mini Zelda game in increments of 1 minute, saving items you collected in each run of 60 seconds. Youll find other houses to start from, enemies and side quests, funny dialogue, and even a new game plus... Only thing is it auto saves once you've beaten the boss and wont let you 100% complete unless done before boss encounter or with a new game. Otherwise Amazing game! Very worth the price and will keep ya busy awhile, fans of story or exploration should pick this up!

I love this game, but that's no surprise with Devolver Digital. I have only one complaint and that's the controls, the movement exclusively. I don't know what it is exactly, but it just feels wrong and I tend to move awkwardly in wrong directions. You guys should implement a stick maybe or some sort of button option for movement. Other than that it's a fantastic fun game which is easy to pick up and quite challenging to master

Always happy to pay for an *actual* game on my phone instead of the ad-ridden freemium baloney this platform is routinely infested with. Especially when it comes from Devolver Digital. The only downsides to this one are the touchscreen controls aren't terribly precise (naturally) and the black & white graphics aren't best for showing what something is or what needs to be done in a time-sensitive game as this. Still, great to play in short bursts. Hope to see more from Devolver on mobile!

Seems like a great port. Only two things I wish was different: keep the screen on, it went off for me while listening to the old dude at the lighthouse and I wish I could switch the analog stick for dpad, kinda hard to make precision moves when you have to swipe to move. Other than that, feels like at home on my phone!

The game is much shorter than I expected. I accidently ended up facing the main bad guy very quickly (in about 2 hours of gameplay) and once you are fighting him, you are stuck there until you win. There are definitely some treasures that I missed, since I finished with only 7 coins and 4 hearts

Great little game about time management. Controls can be a little wonky on this version, but I've always thought it would be a perfect format for a mobile game & it turns out I was right. Really simple, and can be played in 60-second bursts.
